[index] Modifications for KerbalSpaceProgram

Any questions, concerns, mis-identifications, or addendum\'s should be private messaged to the original poster so the thread can be more or less dedicated to the sole act of indexing modifications.

Excessive posts that push down addition notifications will be removed for thread navigation ease.

This thread is a Index for all mods past and present that still work with past and present KSP engines. Any links that do not work should be reported and note of which link as the description, and a note of such will be added to the link.

This is a one-man-band thread; meaning that it is updated to the best of the ability of the person running it. It will be updated frequently and will be sure to cater to all released mods on the forum.

There are other repositories that are completely userbased; see and the The Kerbal Space Program Wiki .

This thread is a work in progress. Currently what\'s being posted now is an update of all categories, which by the end of the day will be filled with all the mods to date (99% complete in indexing); so bear with me.

*[CFG-Edit]*

Realism Mod [v0.3]Stable

-Realism Mod V0.3 - A CFG Edit Mod that creates for harder conditions whilst playing with vanilla parts.

TK31 Liquid Booster Engine

-An enhanced Liquid Booster Engine tweak, that allows for more power whilst retaining liquid fuel conservation.

*[New Parts]*

[Liquid Fuel]

LV-N series Liquid Fuel Nuclear Engines

-A Nuclear Engine, Liquid Fuel edit. It It has a higher thrust then the liquid engine at the cost of dangerous side effects.

The Sphaera Fuel Obtinatus[V0.1_Latest]

-A spherical Liquid Fuel container that weighs a lot, but allows for massive amounts of fuel storage.

MicroEngine

-A small engine ideal for course corrections and reentry burns while orbiting.

LFE-G1

-A uniquely designed spiral Liquid Fuel tank.

Ion Engine!

-A deep space engine that only becomes effective at around 30km - 50km altitude.

FRST-5 Thermal Pump

- Engines heating up too much, yet can\'t afford to drop your thrust? Slap a few of these around your engines and all your woes shall disappear!

Warp Nacelles

-Like the one\'s from Star Trek? You bet your butt.

Gel Thruster Hybrid

-

Ion Thruster

-Want an engine that will let you maneuver in space but takes up almost no room and weighs a tiny amount, Then come to Lucek Astro Engineering LLc for you\'re new Ion Thruster m-486, now in funky tie dye paint job.

BFE-5000 Liquid Engine

- Built to Jebediah\'s exact specifications: 'I want it huge, unstable, prone to overheating and a good chance it will blow up if you look at it from the wrong angle. I didn\'t become an Kerbalnaut for an easy ride, dammit!'. Handle with extreme care (or not at all if you have any sense)
